messages.content: > *The group slips past the flooded plains, through the great mangrove forests, and into the dim, thick air of the swamp*

“I don’t think this is terribly too much better than the spiders. Now everything is sticky.” 

*Mina’s hair suffers the most in this. The curls becoming incredibly frizzy in the humidity and making her look like some kind of pink oversized cotton ball.*

*As they leave the forest behind, Aillig grimaces at the oncoming landscape.* “Never cared for swamps”*He states* “but maybe it’s more that I never cared for the inhabitants of the ones I always had to visit. Perhaps this one will be better. “
*The goblin struggles through the wet ground, making a face as her robe drags*

“Soggyclothes wetfoot sweatybottom phoo.”
*She grumbles to no one in particular*
*Flapjacks slogs along with the ease of one who is comfortable being soaked in filth.*

Her ears are back, and she's more focused on getting through the swamp to the other side than her surroundings.*
*Keyed up from his previous experience in swamps, Aillig keeps on the lookout for anything untoward.*

messages.content: *Mina can barely see through her hair right now. She is mostly just trying to walk in a straight line.*
*The goblin’s hat flops over her eyes, and she mutters, brushing her flat soppy hair out of her eyes*

> *Everyone smells the problem, first.  Rotting flesh mixed with the worst kind of sweat and some fecal matter to boot.  It's a foulness even beyond the fetid, rotting plant stench of the swamp.  Once alerted, it becomes easy to spot most of the slavering undead hiding just above the water to each side of the road.*
> 
> *Fortunately, Aillig spots the two additional undead hiding in the pond nearest to the group before they pounce!*

On a hit, the target takes 4d4 Acid damage and 2d4 Acid damage at the end of its next turn. On a miss, the arrow splashes the target with acid for half as much of the initial damage only.

messages.content: *Pulling out another sigil, Aillig opens it and folds it into a paper dart. His words imbuing it with power he casts it at the remaining undead. Leaving his hand it starts to glow green. Flying true to smacks the undead in the chest, in a splash of acid that continues to bubble and hiss.*

fields.name: Effect
fields.value:
Proficiency with a Glaive allows you to add your proficiency bonus to the attack roll for any attack you make with it.




---


This weapon has the following mastery property. To use this property, you must have a feature that lets you use it.


***Graze.*** If your attack roll with this weapon misses a creature, you can deal damage to that creature equal to the ability modifier you used to make the attack roll. This damage is the same type dealt by the weapon, and the damage can be increased only by increasing the ability modifier.

fields.name: Reckless Attack
fields.value: Melee attacks this turn have advantage. All attacks made against you until the start of your next turn have advantage.

Combat ended.
"Indeed, most unpleasant."
“How creatures come back ? Resurrect not work right?”
*She shuffles over to inspect the nearest corpse, holding her rib over her mouth and nose to block the smell again*
"There are stories of people who got lost in the swamps and resorted to cannibalism, who continued even after death.  Another good reason to pack these..."  *He holds up some cabbage rolls.*

*Saba comes over to Flapjack and reaches up for one of the cabbage rolls, out of goblin range*
“Is food?”
"Yes, this one is venison, I believe."  *Flapjacks offers it with a bow, both hands flat upward.*

*Ra’vek walks over to Aillig* “Nice work with all of that acid.  Hopefully it helps dissolve some of the stench as well”

*He grabs his canteen and takes a swig of water* “So … you mentioned Sigil a bit ago.  That’s actually where I came from recently too.  Are you originally from there?”
*Saba takes the roll reverently and sniffs it, then eats it messily* "Mmph...thank you!"
*Pumpkin pops out to snag a bite as the goblin effectively smears herself in cabbage roll goodness*
*While licking her fingers, she asks Flapjack* "Swamp have undead stinkers always?"
"Yes, though this part is not quite as infested as the area called The Cursed Bog.  It is an accurate name.  Though I did find an interesting variety of skunk cabbage there..."

*Saba seems to gloss over there being a worse swamp and mentally pictures this skunk cabbage. She raises a brow, looking disconcerted*
“Skunk big stinker, cabbage smell like animal or look like? Eat? Or throw?”
"It smells of the animal.  It is not truly a cabbage at all, though it is marginally edible if one is desperate."

*The goblin makes a yech face*
“Hope not ever that hungry.”
"Indeed, friend Saba."

*The goblin looks surprised and tickled pink to be called friend.*
“Mirewatch still far, Friend Flapjack?”
"No, we are quite close, in fact.  Perhaps another ten minutes, at most."

*As the party prepares to head back out, you see Ra’vek kicking mud off his boots.* “I don’t know about you guys, but I’m ready to dry out.  Maybe after a night of good rest we could go find some drier regions to explore.  There’s a desert out here somewhere, right?”
"Ah yes.  When last there I was almost devoured by gigantic sand worms."
“Wow- how did you escape?  I’ve heard those can be extremely deadly.”

*Shaking himself out of a daydream Aillig replies to Ra’vek’s question.* “Yes, I was based out of Sigil. I actually had just entered a portal destined to a place not unlike this swamp when I was… rerouted somehow. I’ve spent most of my life working as a sigil agent based there”
"Amazing that you both came here from the same city."

*Ra’vek was grabbing a quick jerky snack out of his backpack while juggling two conversations.  Hearing Aillig reply, he snaps back his attention towards him.* “Interesting… I thought those portals were reliable.”

*He pauses…* “Do you know of a portal back from here?“

*Ra’vek then looks back to FJ* “Well, my route wasn’t quite as direct… but perhaps that can be solved…”

*And he looks back to Aillig for a reply.*

“I hope I run into you folk more. This was…well the best time I had in a while. Getting to explore finally is doing me wonders.” 

*Mina grins widely at the party, shoving as many of her curls out her face as she can in their current rather fuzzy state.*
"This was quite an adventure, but hey, we all made it out mostly unscathed! Could have been way worse." *Quinn chuckles.*
“Ra’vek continues to chat with his new friends as they happily walk away from the swamp and towards the outpost.*

*The goblin smiles and bows to everyone*
“Always welcome at Mammoth Hut, happy to travels with fine adventurers like you.”
